  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Technical Lead - Entra ID (1 Year Contract)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description </strong></u></p><ul><li>Solution Design & Governance: Define and maintain architecture for hybrid identity (AD + Entra ID). Ensure compliance with corporate security standards and regulatory requirements. </li><li>Technical Leadership: Act as subject matter expert for Entra ID and related technologies (Azure AD, SCCM, Intune). Provide guidance to squads and project teams on identity integration and lifecycle management. </li><li>Operational Excellence: Oversee OU creation, subnet mapping, DFS namespace configuration. Manage synchronization between SCCM and Entra ID; troubleshoot sync issues. </li><li>Stakeholder Coordination: Collaborate with Product Owners, Change Managers and global teams. Support regional deployment and act as proxy product owner for Lift tenants.</li><li>Vendor & Contract Management: Liaise with external partners for managed services and licensing. </li><li>Project Management: Contribute towards regional and global M&A projects on Entra ID scope. </li></ul><p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Solution Design & Governance: Define and maintain architecture for hybrid identity (AD + Entra ID). Ensure compliance with corporate security standards and regulatory requirements. </li><li>Technical Expertise: Deep knowledge of Microsoft Entra ID, Azure AD and Active Directory. Experience with SCCM, Intune, and hybrid identity models.</li><li>Security & Compliance: Familiarity with IAM best practices, MFA, conditional access and zero-trust principles.</li><li>Leadership & Communication: Ability to lead technical discussions and influence stakeholders. Strong communication, documentation and presentation skills.</li><li>Experience: Minimum 7+ years in identity management or similar role.</li><li>Experienced in the context of IT service management and in automation.</li><li>Good understanding of the IS in general, its environments (Windows, Linux, Network, Cloud, Applications...) and standard computer protocols.</li></ul>",
